# Bounded contexts (modular monolith)

Single Maven module; logical boundaries in `dev.vepo.issues.*`. Full table: [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) §Bounded contexts.

## Context map

| Context | Packages |
|---------|----------|
| Platform | `infra` |
| Identity & access | `auth`, `user` |
| Project administration | `project` |
| Workflow configuration | `workflow` |
| Ticket management | `ticket`, `ticket.comments`, `ticket.history`, `ticket.business` |
| Classification | `categories` |
| Notifications | `notifications` |
| Analytics | `dashboards` |
| Email | `mailer` |

## Dependency rules

- Feature packages **may depend on** packages listed in the domain spec for that row.
- **`infra`** must not contain domain logic — only cross-cutting HTTP, errors, dev setup.
- **`..*Repository`** must not depend on `..*Endpoint` ([issues-layered-architecture.mdc](issues-layered-architecture.mdc)).
- Cross-context reactions (notify on ticket move): CDI events or services in the owning context — not direct repository access across unrelated packages.

## Enforcement

`ArchitectureTest` enforces Request/Response naming and record usage. Extend with bounded-context ArchUnit rules when package boundaries stabilize.

## When adding a feature

1. Place code in the correct context package.
2. Update domain spec if new vocabulary.
3. Do not add domain imports to `infra` beyond what cross-cutting requires.
